mule.content:
1. Initial Preparation

When creating a new character, it is recommended to pre-store in the stash items with a good amount of Energy.
These items allow you to equip main skills and support skills as soon as they become available, enabling you to start the game with a main skill linked to up to five supports, plus buff and movement skills.

2. Transfer of Skills and Supports

Skills and supports can also be reused on new characters.
When you acquire a skill/support, it usually comes at a high level, but you can reset it to level 1 and transfer it to another character through the inventory of the purchasing character.

Steps for the transfer:

Open the inventory of the character who owns the skill/support.

Reset the skill level to level 1.

Move the skill/support to the stash.

3. Accessing the Stash via Friends List

From the start of the game, you can access the stash using the friends list:

Press Enter to open the chat.

Click on a friend who is online.

Select the Gift option.

Click the stash icon located in the bottom-right corner of the window.

This method allows the new character to access stored items and skills even in the early stages of progression.
